---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="About — Eidos AGI"
  description="Who built this and why. The people behind the governance infrastructure for AI agents."
>
    <article class="prose-page">
      <header class="page-hero">
        <h1>About</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Who built this.</p>
      </header>

      <section class="content-section">
        <div class="about-people">
          <div class="about-person">
            <img src="/daniel.jpg" alt="Daniel Shanklin" width="80" height="80" class="about-photo" />
            <div>
              <h3>Daniel Shanklin</h3>
              <p class="about-role">Founder</p>
              <p>Patented AI engineer and AGI researcher. Director of AI at AIC Holdings. Holds a patent in cloud algorithm interface design, writes software in 12 languages, and has been building systems for 30+ years. Deep AI and machine learning engineer who started deploying agents into production — data pipelines, investment research, infrastructure automation — and realized nobody had built the governance layer.</p>
              <a href="https://linkedin.com/in/danielshanklin" class="about-link">LinkedIn</a>
            </div>
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Why us</h2>
        <p>We're researchers who build in industry. We deploy agents into production systems — data pipelines, deployment automation, content management, financial analysis — and publish what we learn as open-source tools. Every tool in the Eidos ecosystem exists because we needed it and it didn't exist.</p>
        <p>The trilogy came from running Claude Code sessions that forgot everything between restarts. The forges came from packaging the same setup instructions for the tenth time. The identity protocol came from watching agents operate under borrowed credentials with no audit trail. We build what we need, open-source what we build, and use everything we ship.</p>
      </section>

      <div class="related">
        <span class="related-label">Related</span>
        <div class="related-links">
          <a href="/eidos">Eidos</a>
          <a href="/trilogy">The Trilogy</a>
          <a href="/tools">Tools</a>
          <a href="https://github.com/eidos-agi">GitHub</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </article>
</Base>

<style is:global>
  .about-people { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: var(--space-8); }
  .about-person { display: flex; gap: var(--space-6); align-items: flex-start; }
  .about-photo {
    border-radius: 50%;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    border: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent);
  }
  .about-photo-placeholder {
    width: 80px;
    height: 80px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    border: var(--border-width) solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--color-muted) 20%, transparent);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }
  .about-person h3 { font-size: var(--text-lg); margin-bottom: var(--space-1); }
  .about-role { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-primary); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.06em; margin-bottom: var(--space-3) !important; }
  .about-person p { font-size: var(--text-sm); color: var(--color-muted); line-height: var(--leading-relaxed); margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
  .about-link { font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: var(--text-xs); color: var(--color-muted); }
  @media (max-width: 768px) { .about-person { flex-direction: column; align-items: center; text-align: center; } }
</style>
